     protein_domain  1..12
                     /label="BC2_tag"
                     /synonym="BC2T"
                     /synonym="BC2 tag"
                     /synonym="beta-catenin epitope"
                     /note="12-aa linear epitope tag PDRKAAVSHWQQ (BC2T),
                     corresponding to residues 16–27 of human beta-catenin
                     (UniProt P35222). Bound by the BC2 nanobody (BC2-Nb) with
                     Kd ~1.4 nM via a 'headlock' binding mode: the peptide
                     adopts a beta-strand that integrates into a beta-sheet of
                     the nanobody, providing affinity through backbone hydrogen
                     bonds. Specificity is set by only four side chains (R3, A6,
                     S8, W10, with W10 invariable); the other eight positions
                     tolerate substitution, allowing the tag to be
                     re-engineered. Functions as a single binding epitope with
                     no independently used internal sub-elements."
                     /citation=[1]
